## About

I'm a product designer who believes great software should feel obvious in hindsight. I focus on reducing complexity without reducing capability.

Before design, I studied cognitive science at UC Berkeley, which shapes how I think about information architecture and user mental models.

When I'm not designing, I'm probably hiking, reading sci-fi, or experimenting with ceramics.

